### 2. MPLS On-Path Telemetry Network Action Flag for OAM
* **Slide Presentation:** [02 - MPLS On-Path Telemetry Network Action Flag for OAM](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-mpls-mpls-on-path-telemetry-network-action-flag-for-oam-00)
* **Presenter:** Haoyu Song
* **Relevant Draft:** [draft-ietf-mpls-on-path-telemetry-flag](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-mpls-on-path-telemetry-flag/)

#### Discussion:
* Haoyu Song presented updates on the draft, focusing on postcard-mode telemetry using a single-bit flag (P-bit) to trigger data collection. To ensure ECMP safety, the draft recommends bit position 42, avoiding the first 24 bits of the label stack.
* Greg Mirsky asked how this mechanism differs from IOAM Direct Export (DEX) and alternate marking. 
* Haoyu Song clarified that DEX requires an instruction header in the user packet to specify what data to collect, whereas this proposal uses a single flag to trigger collection of data that is pre-configured out-of-band via the management plane. Haoyu Song added that this approach is complementary to alternate marking and addresses different use cases.

