### 3. Discovering MNA Capabilities Using LSP Ping
* **Slide Presentation:** [03 - Discovering MNA Capabilities Using LSP Ping](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-mpls-03-discovering-mna-capabilities-using-lsp-ping-00)
* **Presenter:** Fabian Sowa

#### Discussion:
* Fabian Sowa presented the updated draft, which has pivoted from using IGP-based signaling to utilizing LSP Ping for discovering In-Stack and Post-Stack MNA capabilities.
* Zafar Ali expressed concern about using LSP Ping for capability discovery, arguing that OAM is not the right tool due to scaling limits, reachability requirements, and the lack of automatic notification upon capability changes.
* Greg Mirsky questioned why a YANG model/management plane interface is not used instead. He also highlighted that in an ECMP environment, the path traversed by LSP Ping might not match the path of actual data flows, calling into question the validity of the collected capability constraints. Greg Mirsky advised against using normative language in the draft.
* Fabian Sowa responded that YANG models and LSP Ping can coexist, as LSP Ping exercises the actual data path. He acknowledged the ECMP challenge and agreed it needs further study in future revisions.

