### 6. Explicit Congestion Notification Using MPLS Network Actions
* **Slide Presentation:** [06 - Explicit Congestion Notification Using MPLS Network Actions](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-mpls-explicit-congestion-notification-using-mpls-network-actions-00)
* **Presenter:** Joel Halpern

#### Discussion:
* Joel Halpern presented a proposal to carry ECN in MNA (both in-stack and post-stack). This resolves a limitation in RFC 5129, where ECN markings consume Traffic Class (EXP) bits and conflict with QoS markings.
* Adrian Farrel (speaking as an individual) clarified that this model mirrors standard IP ECN behavior (congestion-experienced markings propagated from intermediate nodes to the egress, which then notifies the ingress).
* Shuyang Yang expressed strong support for the draft, noting its value for L4S deployments, but questioned why separate opcodes were designated for ISD and PSD.
* Joel Halpern and Greg Mirsky agreed that following early IANA review feedback, the draft will be updated to use a single consolidated opcode for both ISD and PSD.
* Adrian Farrel asked for a show of hands from the room; few participants had read the draft yet, and he encouraged more reviews.

