### 9. Signaling Optimization Objective and Bounded Metrics for MPLS Fast Reroute Backup LSP Tunnels
* **Slide Presentation:** [09 - Signaling Optimization Objective and Bounded Metrics for MPLS Fast Reroute Backup LSP Tunnels](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-mpls-09-signaling-optimization-objective-and-bounded-metrics-for-mpls-fast-reroute-backup-lsp-tunnels-02)
* **Presenter:** Pavan Beeram

#### Discussion:
* Pavan Beeram presented updates to the FAST-FRR extension draft, which defines a new TLV-based FAST-FRR extension object. This object allows the ingress node to signal backup path optimization objectives and metric bounds to the PLR.
* Adrian Farrel asked about the urgency of the requested early IANA code points. Pavan Beeram replied that an implementation is close to shipping, so early code points are highly desirable to facilitate interoperability.
* Zafar Ali questioned the necessity of the draft, arguing that local PLR policies have successfully managed backup path selection for decades, and that adding head-end signaling increases protocol complexity for diminishing returns.
* Pavan Beeram explained that the scale and fluidity of modern TE path profiles have changed significantly, making static local PLR policies insufficient and justifying head-end signaling.
* Zafar Ali asked about interoperability testing partners. Pavan Beeram noted that there are multiple vendors listed as co-authors on the draft.

