## Next Steps

* **`draft-ietf-mpls-on-path-telemetry-flag`:** Authors seek working group feedback on the P-bit position (bit 42) and encoding.
* **Discovering MNA Capabilities Using LSP Ping:** Authors will optimize sub-TLV sizes and further investigate ECMP handling for the next revision.
* **`draft-ietf-mpls-mna-detnet`:** Authors will continue aligning with post-stack MNA specifications and DetNet WG progress on latency formatting.
* **OAM for NRP:** Authors plan to request WG adoption after addressing feedback on the mailing list.
* **Explicit Congestion Notification Using MNA:** Authors will update the draft to use a single consolidated opcode for ISD and PSD and intend to request WG adoption.
* **`draft-ietf-mpls-mna-ioam`:** Authors will present the draft in the IPPM working group session and coordinate a joint WGLC.
* **Signaling RSVP-TE Tunnels on SR-MPLS:** Authors will add clarification text regarding EXP bit propagation and solicit feedback on the list.
* **Signaling Optimization for Backup LSPs:** Authors will formally request WG adoption and early IANA code points on the mailing list.